    descriptionEN:
      "It is the capital and largest city of the Russian Republic of Tatarstan. The city is located at the confluence of the Volga and Kazanka rivers, covers an area of โโ425.3 square kilometers, and has a population of more than 1.2 million, of which approximately 1.6 million reside in the city's metropolitan area. Kazan is the fifth largest city in Russia, and the most populous city on the Volga River. In 1438, Kazan became the capital of the Kazan Khanate. In 1552, Ivan the Terrible captured Kazan and it became part of Russia. It was largely destroyed during the Pugachev Rebellion of 1773-1775, but was later rebuilt during the reign of Catherine II. In the following centuries Kazan grew into a major industrial, cultural and religious center of Russia. In 1920, after the RSFSR became part of the Soviet Union, Kazan became the capital of the Tatar Autonomous Soviet Socialist Republic. After the dissolution of the Soviet Union, Kazan remained the capital of the Republic of Tatarstan.",
