    descriptionEN:
      "This park is located in the west of the Caucasus Mountains and is the second largest national park in Russia. The construction of the Sochi National Park in Sochishinsky dates back to 1953. The fame of the Sochi National Park is due to its biological diversity and the presence of species of animals and plants local to the Siberian region, which transformed this 190,000-hectare park into a unique park. It is found in the Sochi National Park More than 10 waterfalls, including Zamica, Arkhoskoye and Agora waterfalls, and about 200 natural caves. If you go deep into the park, you can see ancient temples and historical ruins, which show that the Sochi-nisky area has been revered by the indigenous people of the region since ancient times. The rest of the land consists of hay fields, pastures, roads and houses. The park is divided into 15 forest areas, united into three large regional groups: Adler, Central and Lazarev. It is a place full of amazing nature where subtropical plants are adjacent to snow-capped mountain peaks.",
