    descriptionEN:
      "Mangrove is a picturesque natural forest, located in the middle of rocks and limestones, located on the banks of the Andaman Sea, on the Malaysian island of Langkawi. The name mangrove is given to it, after the plant spread on the salty beach there. What distinguishes the region is that it contains pure, divine beauty. You will find there many diverse wild animals, water streams, trees and strange-shaped plants, and mysterious caves that adorn the region. You will not feel the distance of the trip itself, as you will be busy enjoying With charming landscapes located on both banks of the water for 3 hours. All you have to do is receive a flashlight from the worker there, and start your journey from the bridge, which extends into the bat cave. Then, when the bridge ends, you will find yourself inside the cave and in front of you is a strange assortment of frightening rock formations, which will terrify your heart, especially because the inside of the cave is shrouded in darkness. After walking a few steps, you will find on the ceiling of these caves a group of frightening bats that you can see by shining a light on them at the top. This is one of the strange adventures that will only happen once in a lifetime. Other than that, the boat takes you to the Thai border in the ocean area, and the area there is indescribably beautiful. It is considered a divine beauty, as it is characterized by an enchanting natural calm and stunning purity that helps the soul to relax and get rid of the worries of life.",
